Coat chicken with 1/2 teaspoon black pepper, salt, and garlic powder. Chill for 4 hours. In a medium bowl, mix together oats, sesame seeds, 1/2 teaspoon salt, chicken granules, and monosodium glutamate. Set aside. In another bowl, combine rice flour, cake flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt, onion powder, basil, oregano, and chicken stock. Dip the bite size chicken into the chicken stock mixture, and roll in sesame seed mixture. Heat oil to 365 degrees F (185 degrees C). Fry the chicken till golden.